The principal manuscript authority for the text of Juvenal is at present inaccessible‚ and our knowledge of it depends chiefly on Pithou's collation in the sixteenth century, when it was at Buda; it is now said to be at Monte Pessulo. It is very carelessly written, as are the ancient Scholia, which seem to rank next in the confidence of the best editors.
